criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  older than 60 and lass than 80 years age;

          -  the elderly should be independent in their ADLs;

          -  be considered able for medical evaluation to participate in the intervention and
             testing protocols;

          -  still not be participating in regular systematized physical activity for at least six
             months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  subjects with any form of transmittable or uncontrolled disease or insulin-dependent
             hypertensive;

          -  unable to perform functional autonomy tests;

          -  women undergo hormonal replacement therapy
